FBIS4-8092 "dreeu069_i_94044" FBIS-EEU-94-069 Daily Report 11 Apr 1994 BOSNIA-HERZEGOVINA Serbs Attack Brcko Serbs Attack Brcko AU1104111294 Sarajevo Radio Bosnia-Herzegovina Network in Serbo-Croatian 0800 GMT 11 Apr 94 AU1104111294 Sarajevo Radio Bosnia-Herzegovina Network Serbo-Croatian BFN [Excerpts] At 0615 this morning the enemy moved into a ferocious tank-infantry attack on Omerbegovaca-Vranovaca line, which was supported substantially by the artillery. Almost simultaneously, the aggressor struck at civilian targets on the free Brcko territory with tanks, howitzers, and 120-mm mortars. All of last night the enemy shelled the entire defense line of the 108th Motorized Brigade. [passage omitted] The enemy is concentrating great amounts of manpower and military hardware on the first lines of the front, especially on Omerbegovaca [word indistinct] line and in the central part of the Brcko battlefield. In the area of [word indistinct], where two Gazela helicopters attacked our positions yesterday, we have observed the arrival of another enemy combat helicopter. The arrival of enemy reinforcements continues.
